Low-Level Design: Distributed Cache System
1. Requirements Clarification
Functional Requirements
Put(key, value) — Store a key-value pair
Get(key) — Retrieve value by key
Delete(key) — Remove a key-value pair
TTL support — Keys expire after a configurable time
Eviction policies — LRU, LFU, or FIFO when memory is full
Non-Functional Requirements
Low latency — Sub-millisecond reads (p99 < 5ms)
High availability — Survive node failures
Scalability — Handle millions of QPS, petabytes of data
Consistency — Tunable (strong vs eventual)
Fault tolerance — No single point of failure
Capacity Estimation
100M daily active users, 10 reads/user/day → ~12K QPS reads
Write:Read ratio = 1:10 → ~1.2K QPS writes
Average key: 50 bytes, value: 1KB → ~1KB per entry
100M keys → ~100GB total data
