9. Pros and Cons Summary
Aspect	Pros	Cons
Consistent Hashing	Minimal data movement on scaling, easy node add/remove	Potential for uneven distribution without virtual nodes
Replication	High availability, read scalability	Write amplification, consistency complexity
LRU Eviction	Simple, effective for temporal locality	Not optimal for frequency-based access patterns
Async Replication	Lower write latency	Risk of data loss, stale reads
Sync Replication	Strong consistency	Higher write latency, availability trade-off
In-Memory Storage	Ultra-low latency	Data loss on crash, limited by RAM
Centralized Proxy	Simpler client, centralized routing logic	Single point of failure, extra network hop
Client-side Hashing	No proxy bottleneck, lower latency	Complex client, harder to update topology
